cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.AR, cs.SE 

The paper discusses fast and scalable solvers for elliptic PDEs, which are typically used in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software). The paper also discusses challenges related to resilience management and energy efficiency, which are relevant to cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
